This PR introduces evp_local.c as the single ownership point for EVP internal cached state, implementing a peek-before-flush discipline that treats committed cache state as an immutable ledger. The peek is a single read-only sweep — it never becomes a second transaction in the chain. The flush only settles when the peek confirms dirty state, using cmp_exch to prevent lost-update races in concurrent contexts such as the TLS handshake_dgst path. On lock-fallback platforms including NonStop, a single write lock covers both validation and settlement — no double-lock, no regression. Depends on #30738, #30670, #30737.

The canonical call sequence for callers across crypto/evp/*.c

```
 * Standard EVP cache access pattern.
 * Peek first — never flush unless peek confirms dirty.
 * Store only after confirmed flush on slow path. */

/* Fast path: single sweep, no lock */
if (ossl_evp_cache_peek(state, &out, lock))
    return out;

/*
 * Slow path: peek missed.
 * Flush confirms and clears stale state if present.
 * Store commits the new value to the ledger. */ if (!ossl_evp_cache_flush(state, lock))
    return NULL;

if (!ossl_evp_cache_store(state, new_val, lock))
    return NULL;

return new_val;
