Contributors guide: https://github.com/openssl/openssl/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md

We want to peek before we ever flush anyway. The order of operations is important in this type of stack to avoid concurrency errors. This is why this PR with the cache and evp is critical and matters as a contribution.
The peek function is meant to sweep once before a flush in the original architecture for the repo context+ by @forloopcodes . The memory here for this context is immutable ledgers vs. the running order book of memory transactions in the stack as the analog for “short” term cache vs. long term commit sort of memory. Again we have to assume that this is a rare problem for the user as it is atomic, but we can “concurrently” still handle not having this peek become a second transaction as it checks the chain, be the context non stop or otherwise with an openssl chain.

